Name: postmenopausal atrophic vaginitis
Definition: A vaginitis that occurs in postmenopausal women and is characterized by vaginal atrophy secondary to estrogen deficiency.

Name: obsolete symptomatic menopausal or female climacteric state
Definition: A vaginitis that occurs in postmenopausal women and is characterized by vaginal atrophy secondary to estrogen deficiency.

Name: bacterial vaginosis
Definition: A vaginitis that is characterized by a grayish vaginal discharge usually of foul odor and the presence of Gardnerella vaginalis.
